profile_positions.description:
Managed Legal department (4 employees & 2 contractors) supporting full scope of Shell Downstream businesses in Russia: (i) Lubricants (distribution of Lubes in CIS); (ii) Lubes supply chain (plant in Torzhok); (iii) Retail (200+ Retail sites); (iv) Aviation.
•	Managed full range of Legal issues and ensured uninterrupted legal support in the areas of 
o	NBD;
o	commercial law (projects and deal negotiations; structuring and termination of JVs); 
o	regulatory compliance, dispute resolution & court proceedings;
o	IP, corporate law & HR;
•	Facilitated implementation of global programs in Trade Control, Ethics & Compliance, Anti-Trust;
•	Managed progression and development of the team by coaching, formal trainings, on-the-job development;
•	Developed cost-effective Legal services function and optimized legal budget;
•	Was recognised at EVP level for effective support to a major commercial initiative.

Provided full range of legal support to non-operated JV (2k staff, 3 Rigs, own pipeline, LNG plant, chartered vessels, helicopters) as member of Contracting & Dispute Resolution Legal team including:
•	Contracting and dispute resolution under English and Russian law;
o	Management of disputes and court proceedings arising out of CP operations;
o	negotiations on Procurement contracts, including major EPC and other construction projects, major maintenance and assets related contracts;
•	Internal governance and cooperation:
o	Legal support to restructuring of CP function and establishment of new CP structure;
o	Development and enhancement of interdepartmental cooperation between Legal and other functions (C&P, tax, finance, business lines);
o	Support to internal audit;
o	Development of contracts and related documents drafts for model contracts library;
o	Development and provision of legal trainings to CP;
•	support to development of Legal personnel (formal trainings, coaching, assistance).

Covered wide range to legal support to Shell unit in Moscow responsible for governance over Russian and Kazakhstan operations focusing predominantly on internal projects and governance issues:
•	Contracting and dispute resolution;
•	Regulatory compliance and corporate issues;
•	Legal support to functions (Finance, External Relations, HR, IT); 
•	Legal support to Kazakhstan operations;
•	Implementation of Ethics and compliance program;
•	Support to Trading related operations and governance.

Contracting support to Trading operations in Russia, internal legal support in liaison with Legal counsel for Trading:
•	Commercial Advisory support to trading activities in Russia (crude oil & products SPAs and storage, logistics);
o	Crude oil and products SPAs;
o	Negotiations with customers;
o	Hedging operations support;
o	Transportation and storage contracts;
•	Other contractual support to Trading business in Russia (all other contracts related to office operations);
•	Regulatory compliance and corporate issues.

Provision of advice to clients on a wide range of issues, including corporate matters (both Russia and overseas jurisdictions), dispute resolution, contracting and regulatory compliance:
•	Corporate issues (establishment and operations of Russian and overseas companies );
•	Commercial matters (contracting and dispute resolution);
•	Customs issues;
•	Regulatory compliance.
